sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70594
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A RFC12 compatible part that simply codes for two stop codons. This part does not have any degradation tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Joseph Lynch
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Made with synthetic oligos: 5' AATTC GCGGCGC T ACTAGT TAATAA GCTAGC A GCGGCCG CTGCA 3' 5' GCGGCCGCTGCTAGC TTATTA ACTAGTAGCGCCGC G 3'
Note that both primers were ordered phosphorylated. An alternative is to phosphorylate the primers yourself with a kinase.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RFC105 A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a standard overhang sequence for in-frame cloning of Proteins of Interest in front or behind an Intein. A detailed cloning strategy is found on the iGEM team Heidelberg 2014's [[http://2014.igem.org/Team:Heidelberg|wiki page]] as well as in RFC[???]. Specifically, this part contains the overhang A used to insert a protein behind any RFC[10] compatible RBS and in-frame with the start-codon. It lies within the four bases formed by the second last base of the XbaI/SpeI scar or the first base in front of start codon respectively and the start codon itself.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Constantin Ahlmann-Eltze, Charlotte Bunne, Magdalena B??scher, Jan Gleixner, Max Horn, Anna Huhn, Nils Klughammer, Jakob Kreft, Elisabeth Sch??fer, Carolin Schmelas, Silvan Schmitz, Max Waldha
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This standard overhang part was developed as part of the iGEM team Heidelberg 2014's Intein Toolbox [[#References[1]]]. All standard sequences can be reviewed in RFC[???] [[#References[2]]].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is only the sequence of a standard overhang. It will not be sent in as physical DNA and was merely created to easily compose new parts in the RFC[???] standard. In the actual cloning process this sequence was and is recommended to be inserted with the according PCR primers.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the sequence of the SpeI/XbaI scar for RBS-CDS junctions in BioBricks standard assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a shorter scar to ensure proper spacing between the RBS and CDS.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
